<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="375" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1441,1971]" pageId="12" pageNumber="375">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1441,1467]" pageId="12" pageNumber="375">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[281,421,1441,1467]" class="Insecta" family="Erotylidae" genus="Episcaphula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[281,421,1441,1467]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="375">Episcaphula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a member of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sen Gupta" authorityYear="1970" box="[644,812,1441,1467]" class="Insecta" family="Erotylidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Megalodacnini">Megalodacnini</taxonomicName>
with the following characters: pronotum lacking posterior marginal bead; pronotum with anterior margin not projecting, not surpassing anterior angles, evenly concave; mentum broadly transverse to rectangularly pentagonal; and tarsi with distinct tarsomere 4. 
<taxonomicName box="[1190,1330,1513,1539]" class="Insecta" family="Erotylidae" genus="Episcaphula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1190,1330,1513,1539]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="375">Episcaphula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from other genera by their smaller size (in general), antennomere 3 only about 1.5× as long as antennomere 2, and tarsomeres 2–3 are little dilated ventrally, tarsomere 3 is not broadly lobed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="375" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1441,1971]" pageId="12" pageNumber="375">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1621,1647]" pageId="12" pageNumber="375">Remarks</emphasis>
. With the raising of the subgenus 
<emphasis box="[697,793,1621,1647]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="375">Orytelus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Heller, K. M." box="[802,945,1621,1647]" pageId="12" pageNumber="375" refId="ref10891" refString="Heller, K. M. (1920 [1918]) Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Erotyliden der indo-australischen Region mit besonderer Berucksichtigung der philippinischen Arten. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, 84 A (8), 1 - 121, 2 pls." type="book" year="1920">Heller, 1920</bibRefCitation>
, to generic status by 
<bibRefCitation author="Chujo, M." box="[1185,1338,1621,1648]" pageId="12" pageNumber="375" pagination="551 - 573" refId="ref10552" refString="Chujo, M. (1968) Erotylid beetles from Thailand, Laos, and Vietnam. Studies on the erotylid beetles (21). Pacific Insects, 10 (3 - 4), 551 - 573." type="journal article" year="1968">Chûjô (1968)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Erotylidae" genus="Episcaphula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="375">Episcaphula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is left with five subgenera comprised of approximately 95 species in Asia (
<bibRefCitation author="Chujo, M. &amp; Chujo, M." box="[1049,1302,1657,1684]" pageId="12" pageNumber="375" pagination="139 - 185" refId="ref10626" refString="Chujo, M. &amp; Chujo, M. (1988 b) A catalog of the Erotylidae (Insecta, Coleoptera) from the Old World (excl. the Ethiopian Region). Esakia, 26, 139 - 185." type="journal article" year="1988">Chûjô &amp; Chûjô 1988b</bibRefCitation>
), 39 species in African tropics (
<bibRefCitation author="Delkeskamp, K." box="[363,571,1693,1719]" pageId="12" pageNumber="375" pagination="1 - 65" refId="ref10743" refString="Delkeskamp, K. (1981) Erotylidae von Africa und Madagascar. Coleopterorum Catalogus Supplementum, 34, 1 - 65." type="journal article" year="1981">Delkeskamp 1981</bibRefCitation>
), but no members in the New World. Species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1118,1258,1693,1719]" class="Insecta" family="Erotylidae" genus="Episcaphula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1118,1258,1693,1719]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="375">Episcaphula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1327,1436,1693,1719]" name="Indonesia" pageId="12" pageNumber="375">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
were reviewed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Heller, K. M." box="[362,518,1729,1755]" pageId="12" pageNumber="375" refId="ref10891" refString="Heller, K. M. (1920 [1918]) Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Erotyliden der indo-australischen Region mit besonderer Berucksichtigung der philippinischen Arten. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, 84 A (8), 1 - 121, 2 pls." type="book" year="1920">Heller (1920)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Chujo, M. &amp; Chujo, M." box="[530,802,1729,1755]" pageId="12" pageNumber="375" pagination="25 - 37" refId="ref10592" refString="Chujo, M. &amp; Chujo, M. (1988 a) Erotylidae from New Guinea and her adjacent islands II (Coleoptera). Esakia, 26, 25 - 37." type="journal article" year="1988">Chûjô &amp; Chûjô (1988a)</bibRefCitation>
had begun revisionary work on the New 
<collectingCountry box="[1278,1359,1729,1755]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="12" pageNumber="375">Guinea</collectingCountry>
fauna, described additional species and stated there are many more undescribed species. Unfortunately, no more current work has been published on the group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1441,1971]" pageId="12" pageNumber="375">
Even with five subgenera, the remaining species of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Episcaphula)" box="[802,1111,1837,1863]" class="Insecta" family="Erotylidae" genus="Episcaphula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Episcaphula">
<emphasis box="[802,942,1837,1863]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="375">Episcaphula</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[962,1102,1837,1863]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="375">Episcaphula</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
show a large amount of diversity in body size, color patterns, surface structure (setose vs. glabrous), antennal characters, pronotal puncture patterns, etc., indicating it remains a large conglomerate of taxa needing further study at a generic level. Until more studies and additional analyses are made, we prefer to retain the current subgenera of 
<taxonomicName box="[1111,1251,1945,1971]" class="Insecta" family="Erotylidae" genus="Episcaphula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1111,1251,1945,1971]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="375">Episcaphula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
